# ImGui Module

## Module Purpose and Responsibilities

The ImGui module provides a Dear ImGui overlay that runs on top of the engine's layer stack. Its sole responsibility is to initialise the Dear ImGui context, wire it to the Win32 window and DirectX 11 device, bracket every frame with `NewFrame`/`Render` calls, and tear everything down cleanly on shutdown.

The module is intentionally narrow: it owns no game logic. All actual ImGui widget calls (windows, controls, plots, etc.) are the responsibility of the caller — typically ECS systems inside `SandboxApp` — which issue them between `Begin()` and `End()`.

The module is **excluded from `Testing` builds** via the `#ifndef TESTS_ENABLED` guard in `Application::Init()` and `Application::Data`. No unit tests exist for this module.

